> If nothing says "date night" like a juicy steak, then this dish is the equivalent of getting down on one knee. Here, melt-in-your-mouth beef tenderloin (the same cut as filet mignon!) is seared and then drizzled with a rich balsamic pan sauce (cue the swoons). On the side, there's crisp roasted broccoli and creamy chive-flecked mashed potatoes. No matter who you cook this for, we have a good feeling they'll be quite smitten.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Mince @chives{¼%ounce}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and add @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, half the chives, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved cooking liquid as needed, until smooth and creamy. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

While potatoes cook, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Beef Tenderloin ==

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until a crust begins to form, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Remove from heat; transfer beef to a #plate{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

== Balsamic Steak Sauce ==

Add @beef demi-glace{1%unit}, half the @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and @water{¼%cup} to pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide beef, broccoli, and mashed potatoes between plates. Drizzle beef with sauce. Garnish with remaining chives and serve.